OL,3,CChildren's social care reforms to
OL,4,Cinclude rules to stop profiteering
OL,6,F"They need action without delay, not
OL,7,Fplans or strategies, so I welcome the
OL,8,Furgency with which this Government is
OL,9,Fsetting out plans to tackle some of
OL,10,Fthe most entrenched challenges."
OL,12,FEducation Secretary Bridget Phillipson
OL,13,Fsaid: "Our care system has suffered
OL,14,Ffrom years of drift and neglect.
OL,16,F"It's bankrupting councils, letting
OL,17,Ffamilies down, and above all, leaving
OL,18,Ftoo many children feeling forgotten,
OL,19,Fpowerless and invisible.
