OL,6,F"We want to break down the barriers to
OL,7,Fopportunity and end the cycle of
OL,8,Fcrisis through ambitious reforms to
OL,9,Fgive vulnerable children the best life
OL,10,Fchances ` because none of us thrive
OL,11,Funtil all of us do."
OL,13,FThe Children's Charities Coalition,
OL,14,Fwhich includes Action for Children,
OL,15,FBarnardo's and the NSPCC, said the
OL,16,FGovernment's "commitment to reforming
OL,17,Fand rebalancing children's social care
OL,18,Ftowards early intervention and family
OL,19,Fsupport services, is a huge step
OL,20,Fforward in fixing a struggling system
OL,21,Funder immense strain".
